  "id": "019d2de4-49de-7180-b6dc-94c728ffa50c",
  "content": "# Composite Scoring & Decay Mathematics for Tier Classification (Research, March 2026)\n\n## Composite Score Formula (Recommended for corvia)\n\n```\nR(entry) = w_d * D(t, alpha_type) * C(confidence)\n         + w_a * A(access_count, last_accessed)\n         + w_g * G(entry)\n         + w_i * I(entry)\n```\n\nWeights: w_d=0.40, w_a=0.25, w_g=0.20, w_i=0.15\n\n## Decay Function: Power-Law (Recommended)\n\n`D(t) = (1 + t_days)^(-alpha)` — chosen over exponential for fat-tail property (Cold entries never fully vanish, enabling reversible promotion).\n\nAlpha values per memory type:\n- Structural: 0 (no decay), Procedural: 0.10, Decisional: 0.15, Analytical: 0.30, Episodic: 0.60\n\n## Confidence Modulation\n\n`effective_decay = D(t) * confidence^beta` with beta=1.0 (linear). Low confidence accelerates tier demotion.\n\n## Tier Thresholds with Hysteresis\n\nDemotion: Hot->Warm at R<0.45, Warm->Cold at R<0.20, Cold->Forgotten at R<0.03\nPromotion: Warm->Hot at R>=0.55, Cold->Warm at R>=0.30, Forgotten->Cold at R>=0.10\nGap of 0.10 prevents oscillation. Additionally require 2 consecutive GC cycles above threshold before promotion (ARMS hot-age filter).\n\n## Graph Connectivity Signal\n\nUse weighted degree centrality for GC scorer (O(1) per node). Reserve PageRank (O(E*30 iterations)) for weekly batch importance refresh.\n\n## Key Sources\n\n- Park et al. Generative Agents: score = recency + importance + relevance (equal weights, min-max normalized, decay factor 0.995/hour)\n- Hindsight TEMPR: 4-channel RRF with k=60, temporal link decay exp(-dt/sigma_t), asymmetric confidence updates\n- ARMS: dual EWMA (alpha_s=0.7, alpha_l=0.1), cost/benefit promotion, hot-age >= 2 consecutive intervals\n- Power-law > exponential for memory systems: fat tail means old entries decay proportionally slower (Kahana & Adler 2002)\n- Redis Agent Memory: threshold-based only (max_age=90d, max_inactive=30d, budget=10K), no continuous scoring",
